                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_107096">Ravenstone</placeName>.
                         
                        Indenture by which <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Golone</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_107096">R<supplied>avenstone</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Golone">
                           <forename>Alice</forename> his wife</persName> grant to <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename> 
                           <surname>Ode</surname>
                        </persName> of the same and <persName nymRef="Ode">
                           <forename>Isabella</forename> his wife</persName>, and <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> le <surname>Fullere</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Fullere">
                           <forename>Agnes</forename> his wife</persName>, an acre of land in <placeName key="place_107096">R<supplied>avenstone</supplied>
                        </placeName> between <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Tone</surname>
                        </persName>â€™s land and that of <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> 
                           <surname>Eve (or Ene)</surname>
                        </persName> at <placeName type="minor">Fonleslow</placeName>. Rent: a rose at Midsummer, for 12 years, and after that 13/-. 
                        Witnesses: Henry de ... 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Alewey</surname>
                        </persName>,
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Philip</forename> 
